Carlic Carrot Brown Rice
source|Silvia Ribas
url|https://gardeninthekitchen.com/garlicky-carrot-brown-rice/
aliases|
tags|
activeTime|
totalTime|
yield|6-8 servings
description|

# ingredients
1|cup|brown rice
2.5|cup|water
2|tbsp|olive oil
1||small onion, diced
2||garlic cloves, minced
1/4|tsp|sea salt
1/2|tsp|onion powder
2||med carrots, cubed

# instructions
Heat oil in a medium pan.
Add onions and sauté until translucent.
Add garlic, carrots, salt and onion powder.
Stir and sauté for 2 minutes.
Add brown rice, continue to stir and sauté until all the rice has been saturated with the oil, garlic and onion mixture (about 1-2 mins) then add the wetter and cover.
Cook on medium low for 40 minutes or until all the liquid has absorbed. Stir once or twice in between.
